  "status": "Review",
  "summary": "This ERC proposes an extension to the [ERC-20](./eip-20.md) token standard by adding Encumber\u2014the ability for an account to grant another account exclusive right to move some portion of their balance. Encumber is a stronger version of [ERC-20](./eip-20.md) allowances. While [ERC-20](./eip-20.md) approve grants another account the permission to transfer a specified token amount, encumber grants the same permission while ensuring that the tokens will be available when needed.",
  "title": "Encumber - Splitting Ownership & Guarantees"
}